rtTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104exw1665703011498.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exw1665703011498.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exw1665703011498.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"exw1665703011498\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $status\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"exw1665703011498___status_290369\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return or set the current condition code.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"exw1665703011498__topic_d89669e1_d89670e1_d89671e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89672e1_d89673e1_d89674e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89675e1_d89676e1_d89677e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__section_w1554ab1b7b5_w1555ab1b7_w1556ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89678e1_d89679e1_d89680e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">if ($status &lt; 0)</code> ...</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exw1665703011498__topic_d59662e1_d59663e1_d59664e1_d59665e1_d59666e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d635713e87\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89684e1_d89685e1_d89686e1\">An integer value. If a decimal value is assigned to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, Uniface rounds it to the nearest integer.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exw1665703011498__topic_d59667e1_d59668e1_d59669e1_d59670e1_d59671e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d635713e99\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exw1665703011498__topic_d59672e1_d59673e1_d59674e1_d59675e1_d59676e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d635713e109\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89696e1_d89697e1_d89698e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> returns a condition code that indicates the result of a runtime action, such as an I/O request. In general:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exw1665703011498__li_d35714e1_d35715e1_d35716e1\">A negative value in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> indicates an error. In this case, the function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> gives further information about the cause of the error and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span> gives details about the exact location where the error occurred.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exw1665703011498__li_d35717e1_d35718e1_d35719e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> indicates a successful operation.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exw1665703011498__li_d35720e1_d35721e1_d35722e1\">A positive value indicates a warning or information.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89699e1_d89700e1_d89701e1\">Although you can assign a value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> to pass codes to another ProcScript module or component, doing so resets the current value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>, so the ProcScript error status and context are lost.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89702e1_d89703e1_d89704e1\">In the Debugger, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> can be accessed directly or as variable <code class=\"ph codeph\">$100</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exw1665703011498__topic_d59677e1_d59678e1_d59679e1_d59680e1_d59681e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d635713e163\">\n                       \n ProcScript Modules and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89708e1_d89709e1_d89710e1\">Each time a ProcScript module is activated, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>. When the ProcScript module ends, Uniface checks <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, because the value can influence what happens next.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89711e1_d89712e1_d89713e1\">The end value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> has different effects with different triggers. For example, if the ProcScript code in a remove trigger ends with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> less than <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>, the occurrence is not removed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89714e1_d89715e1_d89716e1\">If the module was invoked by a statement, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">call</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span>, the return value of the module is assigned to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>. If the module was invoked using an inline construction (such as an instance handle or a function argument), the return value is returned inline, and the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> keeps the value as set inside the Proc module.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exw1665703011498__p_d89717e1_d89718e1_d89719e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gkd1665702624564.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gkd1665702624564.html\" title=\"ProcScript modules return a numeric status value in $status. This module may contain the value given as an argument to the return or exit statement, a value that indicates successful completion of a command or module, or a negative number that reflects an error.\">Return Values, Status Values, and ProcScript Errors</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exw1665703011498__section_ezm_dy3_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d635713e230\">Example: Conditional Processing Based on <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span></h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example inspects the value of\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, set by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement in the\n               Store trigger. The check on <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> allows the ProcScript to\n               handle error situations.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"exw1665703011498__pre_mqc_2y3_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; Store trigger\nstore\nif ($status &lt; 0)\n message \"Store error number %%$status.\"\n rollback\nelse\n message \"Store complete.\"\n commit\nendif\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etu1719376772254.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>= (compute)</a><p>Assigns the value of an expression to a field, variable, or function.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ckg1665702579864.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>return</a><p>Exit from the ProcScript module, optionally returning a value to $status.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kgi1665702560769.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>store</a><p>Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hms1665702684501.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$dberror</a><p>Return the error code reported by the DBMS.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gst1665702684426.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$error</a><p>Returns the Uniface message number for the error.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ypd1665702576258.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$procerror</a><p>Return the reason for an error in ProcScript execution.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/opq1665702649630.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$procerrorcontext</a><p>Return the location of the error specified by $procerror.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncx1686824523526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$result</a><p>Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$status Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $status Return or set the current condition code. $status $status = Expression Example: if ($status < 0) ... Return Values An integer value. If a decimal value is assigned to $status , Uniface rounds it to the nearest integer. Use Allowed in all component types. Description $status returns a condition code that indicates the result of a runtime action, such as an I/O request. In general: A negative value in $status indicates an error. In this case, the function $procerror gives further information about the cause of the error and $procerrorcontext gives details about the exact location where the error occurred. 0 indicates a successful operation. A positive value indicates a warning or information. Although you can assign a value of $status to pass codes to another ProcScript module or component, doing so resets the current value of $procerror , so the ProcScript error status and context are lost. In the Debugger, $status can be accessed directly or as variable $100 . ProcScript Modules and $status Each time a ProcScript module is activated, $status is set to 0 . When the ProcScript module ends, Uniface checks $status , because the value can influence what happens next. The end value of $status has different effects with different triggers. For example, if the ProcScript code in a remove trigger ends with $status less than 0 , the occurrence is not removed. If the module was invoked by a statement, such as call or activate , the return value of the module is assigned to $status . If the module was invoked using an inline construction (such as an instance handle or a function argument), the return value is returned inline, and the value of $status keeps the value as set inside the Proc module. For more information, see Return Values, Status Values, and ProcScript Errors . Example: Conditional Processing Based on $status The following example inspects the value of $status , set by the store statement in the Store trigger. The check on $status allows the ProcScript to handle error situations. ; Store trigger store if ($status < 0) message \"Store error number %%$status.\" rollback else message \"Store complete.\" commit endif Copy Related Links = (compute) Assigns the value of an expression to a field, variable, or function. return Exit from the ProcScript module, optionally returning a value to $status. store Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers. $dberror Return the error code reported by the DBMS. $error Returns the Uniface message number for the error. $procerror Return the reason for an error in ProcScript execution. $procerrorcontext Return the location of the error specified by $procerror. $result Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}